For this reason, a coup situation resembles, in a vague sort of way, a cross-ruff situation, in that the side suits must be led out first so as not to give the Opponents any chance to throw off losers. At the same time, the side suits cannot be eliminated too quickly, for they may be needed for communication purposes - their high cards serve as needed entries. |
PG| ***** 106 ***** |


